        -> peer-to-peer Model: Peer-to-peer systems also have different types, based on how peers discover and communicate with each other.
            -> Type 1: Pure Peer-to-Peer
                -> In this there is no central server and all peers are equal and each peer can discover and communicate with other directly.
                -> Example Early file-sharing system
                -> Characteristics: Fully decentralized, No SPOF, Difficult peer discovery and coordination.
                                +-------+ <----> +-------+
                                | Peer1 | <----> | Peer2 |
                                +-------+ <----> +-------+
                                     ^        ↕        ^
                                     |        ↕        |
                                +-------+ <----> +-------+
                                | Peer3 | <----> | Peer4 |
                                +-------+ <----> +-------+


            -> Type 2: Hybrid Peer-to-Peer
                -> In this a central service is used for coordination, and actual data transfer happens directly between peers.
                -> The central server may maintain a list of peers and hep with discovery.
                -> Example: Torrent tracker
                -> Characteristics: Partial dependency on central components
                                           +----------------+
                                           | Tracker /      |
                                           | Discovery Svc  |
                                           +----------------+
                                                ↑     ↑
                                                |     |
                                     +-------+  |     |  +-------+
