                                     +-------+            +-------+
                                           ↕                  ↕
                                        +-------+ <------> +-------+
                                        | Peer3 | <------> | Peer4 |
                                        +-------+          +-------+


            -> Type 3: Structured Peer-to-Peer
                -> In this peer follow a specific structure or algorithm
                -> It often uses in Distributed Hash Table(DHT)
                -> Example: Advanced file-sharing systems
                -> Characteristics: Complex implementation

            -> Type 4: Unstructured Peer-to-Peer
                -> In this no fixed structure and peer connected randomly and searches may involve broadcasting queries.

